*PENDING SALE 03/20/2018* I will update if anything changes

They restored the military bluing(from a grey parkerized finish), added historically correct selector notches and Serbian markings, serialized the bolt & dust cover to match with the receiver, removed parkerizing from the bolt, carrier & the top of the leaf sight. I also have a surplus set of M70B1 wood furniture on it. 
This rifle has proven itself to be a great shooter and very accurate before I decided to send it to be refinished. I have not been able to take it out since getting it back so it's still really new looking. I asked them to re-do any canting of the sights that they could see so I imagine it's even better now. The bore is in awesome shape with no pittng or rust.
The only negative things I can think of are there's very tiny bit of play in the lower handguard and the gas piston by the gas tube shows a bit of wear from use/age but nothing that affects function.
 
Comes with:
5 new production 30rd steel Serbian & Croatian Yugo Bolt Hold open style magazines. They appear to be every bit as durable and reliable as the surplus steel mags.
Yugoslavian AK Bayonet (without the leather frog)
Romanian sling
Soft case
The rifle has a Century RAK-1 trigger group, Power Custom Hammer/Trigger retainer plate, and an ALG defense heavy recoil spring added for shootability and reliability.
